INSERT INTO `cj_team` VALUES (4,'Gerard (Jerry) Condon','President','d70a0546510a4ad38d2534c79f1aff4f.jpg','Jerry has enjoyed a highly successful 30 year career in the construction industry. Having started out at Tishman Construction of New York, he moved to the West Coast in 1984 to manage the construction of several large hotel and luxury condominium projects. In the 10 years prior to joining Condon-Johnson, Jerry managed large Public Works projects for Conco Cement Company, including the San Francisco International Terminal Foundations, North Concord BART Station, and the Millbrae BART Station.  In 2002, Jerry became President of Condon-Johnson and has overseen the continued growth of the company since that time.\r\nJerry has a BA degree from Fordham University and a BS degree in Civil Engineering from San Diego State University.\r\n','2016-10-13 08:58:21'),(5,'James Johnson','Vice President','2d2a973bfdb9e310aba6bdbeb657496e.jpg','James  plays a major role in developing the technical and innovative strategies for which Condon-Johnson & Associates (CJA) has become so well respected. He has directly supervised more than 200 job sites and has a special knack for the innovative application of established techniques as well as an expert ability to assess and implement new technologies.\r\nIn 1985, James joined Mike Condon in assuming responsibility for the growth of Kulchin and Associates, Inc. He spent three years as the Area Manager for Los Angeles and in 1990 became Executive Vice President of what was then Kulchin-Condon & Associates, Inc.\r\nHe began his career with a BSCE degree from the University of California at Davis and upon graduation, he joined Peter Kiewit & Sons as an engineer in the area of foundation and underground construction. James served two terms as President of the West Coast Chapter of The International Association of Foundation Drilling and is currently serving a second term on the Deep Foundations Institute’s Board of Directors.\r\n','2016-10-13 09:23:33'),(6,'Jeremy Condon','Vice President / Operations Manager','5e85a2e73a8ea04a15f8b57ed4a64a1c.jpg','Jeremy has spent 18 years at Condon-Johnson & Associates working in all facets of field operations throughout the company’s four Districts. Currently, Jeremy serves as the General Superintendent for the Northern California District as well as coordinating overall field operations for the entire company, a role that entails coordinating equipment and field personnel with all the District General Superintendents and Project management personnel.\r\nAs a principal of the company, Jeremy has the authority to allocate resources to ensure construction projects are properly staffed in order to fulfill Condon-Johnson’s contractual responsibilities. Jeremy proactively supports, encourages, and facilitates staff to improve performance on all projects and ensure Condon-Johnson is meeting the high expectations our clients.\r\n','2016-10-13 09:24:14'),(7,'Mansoureh Mohebali','Controller','af2a319fbc44526f23bae60d221b5cd5.jpg','Mansoureh joined Condon-Johnson & Associates (CJA) as Controller in 1993. With her considerable experience as a financial manager in the construction sector, Mansoureh has primary responsibility for business performance analysis, and business planning support. Among her other duties, Mansoureh oversees budgeting, cash flow management, insurance risk management, and forecasting.\r\nBefore joining CJA, Mansoureh worked for Piombo Corporation, becoming Comptroller in 1986. Mansoureh has a BS in Business Administration Cum Laude from the University of Tehran and an MBA in Accounting from San Francisco State University.\r\n','2016-10-13 09:24:58'),(8,'Dominic Parmantier, P.E.','Regional Vice President Northwest','9e24ac7ee9398cd34896a7a73097cc78.jpg','Dominic joined Condon-Johnson & Associates (CJA) as a Project Manager in 2003. Based in the Seattle office, Dominic specializes in assessment and implementation of ground improvement methods as well as conventional anchored earth retention and drilled shafts. He was directly involved on the Reno Transportation Rail Access Corridor (RETRAC), Beacon Hill Tunnel, 505 1 st Ave CSM Project, the Sound Transit U-220 Tunnel, and the Ground Based Missile Defense (GBD) at Fort Greeley, Alaska.\r\nDominic has estimated and managed numerous projects that involved geo-technical design for ground improvement, anchored earth retention, and permanent foundations. Projects have included micro-piles, anchored earth retention, slurry walls, compaction grouting, cement grouting, chemical grouting, jet grouting, deep soil mixing, and vibro-replacement stone columns.\r\nPrior to CJA, Dominic worked for Hayward Baker and for Schnabel Foundation Company. He had extensive experience with several grouting techniques, anchored earth retentions, and micropiles in a variety soil conditions encountered while working on sites from Detroit to British Columbia to Honolulu. \r\nDominic has a BSCE from the University of Portland, Oregon and an MSCE from Virginia Polytechnic Institute and State University, Blacksburg Virginia. He is a licensed Civil Engineer in the State of Washington, Oregon, California, and Idaho.\r\n','2016-10-13 09:25:34'),(9,'George Burrough, P.E.','Regional Vice President Southern California','335c1d80b13d8aba16d2d74538d5b121.jpg','George joined Condon-Johnson & Associates (CJA) as District Manager for the San Diego office upon its opening in 1999. An expert in shoring, George’s strong problem solving skills and expert project management can be seen in numerous projects throughout CJA’s four regions but especially in Southern California.\r\nGeorge has extensive experience in design/build, deep foundation, earth support (both permanent and temporary) and slope stabilization projects. George has estimated and managed major projects including seawalls, temporary earth retaining structures, demolition and excavation, permanent shotcrete retaining walls, and drilled foundations. George has estimated and managed projects for many public and private sector clients including the US Navy, CALTRANS and Bosa Developments. Prior to joining CJA, he worked for Wagner Construction Co., starting as a Project Engineer and rising to District Manager within four years.\r\nGeorge is a licensed Civil Engineer in the State of California and has been both the Engineer of Record and Supervisor on the design of numerous earth retention projects. George received a BSCE in 1995 at San Diego State University.\r\n','2016-10-13 09:26:25'),(10,'Keith Bizzack','Oakland District Manger','46ddecf82a71a2b3abb2c9d2dce11ce3.jpg','Keith joined the Los Angeles Office of Condon-Johnson & Associates (CJA)  in 1995 having previously worked at Dillingham Construction. In 1997 he transferred to the Oakland office to work on the San Francisco International Airport expansion project, and since that time has managed a wide range of projects including bridge foundations work, large internally braced excavations, slope stabilizations, and permanent and temporary earth retention projects. He has over 25 years experience in estimating and managing heavy civil construction and engineering, and has managed multiple projects with many different clients such as the City of San Francisco, EBMUD, Santa Clara VTA, Swinerton Builders, Pankow, McCarthy, Bechtel Infrastructure, and Webcor Builders. Keith was promoted to District Manager for the Northern California office in 2007.\r\nKeith has a Bachelor’s degree in Architectural Engineering from the University of Colorado, Boulder.\r\n','2016-10-13 09:27:04'),(11,'Mark Morrison','Vice President – Corporate Estimating Manager','a279684732cf4a6813b3468be701801d.jpg','Mark joined the Condon-Johnson & Associates (CJA) Oakland office in 1992 as a project engineer and today holds the role of Corporate Estimating Manager. Mark has used his extensive experience in anchored earth support (permanent and temporary) and slope stabilization for a wide variety of public and private works for clients such as CALTRANS, Department of General Services for the State of California, PG&E, and the Legacy Fund.\r\nHe has estimated and managed a number of major projects including seawalls, highway slope stabilization, drainage shafts, and permanent and temporary earth retention projects, and his full range of construction expertise includes demolition, excavation, permanent shotcrete retaining walls, and drilled foundations.\r\nPrior to joining CJA, Mark worked for Kiewit Pacific Co. as a project engineer. He holds a BS in Construction Management from the University of Cincinnati.\r\n','2016-10-13 09:27:48'),(12,'Mike Almeida','Special Projects','9858b975b0c7a3ed20b4ba606a982099.jpg','Mike joined Condon-Johnson in 2005 and took over our rapidly expanding Stone Column Division. Working in Ground Improvement, he is responsible for streamlining all aspects of our Stone Column work throughout the western states. Mike brings 27 years’ experience in Heavy/Civil/Building construction both domestic and overseas to CJA.\r\nAfter receiving a BSCE degree from Worcester Polytechnic Institute, Mike began his career with SJ Groves, followed by seven years with Perini Construction both overseas and in California and 18 years with Conco Cement Company. Mike’s extensive experience includes construction work on dams, bridges, highways, building structures and refineries.\r\n','2016-10-13 09:28:31'),(13,'Spark Johnston, P.E.','Senior Director of Micropiles and Specialized Small Diameter Drilling','89be4c7b3dfab65450986259977df3a0.jpg','Spark has been in the engineering and construction industry for over 35 years. During that time, Spark has participated as a project engineer, estimator, project manager and/or operations manager on a variety of temporary/permanent earth retention systems, drilled and grouted deep foundation systems, ground improvement/treatment systems and landslide stabilization systems. He has been responsible for specialty design/build projects ranging in value from $20,000 to $15,000,000. Spark has designed and managed several specialty geotechnical projects throughout the United States including soldier pile and tie-back walls, high capacity anchored caisson walls, soil nailed walls, cantilevered soldier pile walls, high capacity tiedown anchors for dam stabilization, large diameter drilled shafts, grout stabilization, vibro flotation techniques for ground improvement and high capacity micropiles for bridge and building support.\r\nSpark is a licensed Civil Engineer in the State of Washington, Oregon, and Alaska. Spark received a BSCE at San Jose State University.\r\n','2016-10-13 09:29:11'),(14,'Peter Alhorn, P.E.','Design Build Engineering Manager','1f31ee3944c092bcc094c513494cab67.jpg','Peter joined the Oakland office of Condon-Johnson & Associates in 1998. He has 30 years’ experience designing, constructing, and estimating a wide range of deep excavations and shoring systems. Currently, he is the Engineering Manager for CJA, and provides in-house design services that provide innovative applications of CJA’s expertise and equipment to the foundation industry.\r\nPrior to joining CJA, Peter was Chief Estimator and Engineer for Homer J. Olsen, Inc., and also worked with Ben C. Gerwick, Inc. and Berti-Lindquist Consulting Engineers providing consulting services to Contractors. Peter received a BSCE in 1976 and MSCE in 1978 from UC Berkeley, as well as a MBA from Berkeley in 1987, and is a licensed Civil Engineer in California and Nevada\r\n','2016-10-13 09:30:01');
